# Tailwind CSS and Light/Dark Mode

## Styling

- **Use only Tailwind CSS classes** for layout, spacing, colors, typography, and responsive design.
- Do not add custom CSS (e.g. raw CSS modules or inline styles) unless Tailwind cannot achieve the result.
- Prefer Tailwind utility classes over Tamagui style props for visual styling when both are available.

## Responsive (Web + Mobile Web)

- **Design for both desktop and mobile web.** Use Tailwind breakpoints: `sm:` (640px), `md:` (768px), `lg:` (1024px), `xl:` (1280px).
- Prefer fluid layouts: `w-full` with `max-w-*` where needed; use responsive padding (e.g. `px-4 sm:px-6 md:px-8 lg:px-16`).
- Touch targets on mobile: interactive elements should be at least 44×44px (`min-h-11 min-w-11` or `min-h-12`). Use `touch-manipulation` to reduce tap delay.
- Use `min-h-dvh` for full-height on mobile (accounts for browser chrome); pair with `md:min-h-screen` if needed.
- Avoid horizontal overflow: use `overflow-x-hidden` on root when appropriate; test on narrow viewports (320px–400px).

## Light and Dark Mode

- **Always support both light and dark mode** in UI and components.
- Use Tailwind’s `dark:` variant for dark-mode styles, e.g. `bg-white dark:bg-zinc-950`, `text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100`.
- Test and verify appearance in both themes during development.
- Theme is controlled via `NextThemeProvider`; the `dark` class on `<html>` drives Tailwind’s `dark:` variant.

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ Good: Tailwind only, light + dark
<div className="rounded-lg bg-white p-4 shadow dark:bg-zinc-900 dark:shadow-zinc-800">
  <h2 className="text-lg font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-zinc-100">Title</h2>
  <p className="text-zinc-600 dark:text-zinc-400">Description</p>
</div>
```

```tsx
// ❌ Avoid: inline styles or non-Tailwind CSS for layout/colors
<div style={{ background: 'white', padding: 16 }}>...</div>
```
